Notes on using transit_access.py

1. Install python3

   For example, on Ubuntu:
     apt-get install python3

2. Install python3 packages Python Imaging Library (PIL) and pygtfs

   For example:
     apt-get install python3-pil
     pip3 install pygtfs

3. Get WMATA GTFS data:
   http://www.wmata.com/rider_tools/developer_resources.cfm

4. Convert GTFS data to pygtfs format:

   For example:
     ~/.local/bin/gtfs2db append wmata_gtfs.zip gtfs.sqlite
   (takes a long time)

5. Run the script
   ./transit_access.py

   An image will be generated in the same directory.

